<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/130500-many-historians-have-reexamined-and">Many historians have reexamined and abandoned the notion that Africa was always primitive and poor. John K. Thornton, for example, argues that Africa&#39;s backwardness is a recent phenomenon; before perhaps the 18th century, societies in sub-Saharan Africa were just as advanced as those in Europe or Asia. How does this square with Diamond&#39;s theory that Africa was geographically predisposed to poverty and backwardness?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_130500'><a id="like_count_community_question_130500" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/130500?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">8 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F1842.Guns_Germs_and_Steel">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/130500-many-historians-have-reexamined-and">7 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/130500-many-historians-have-reexamined-and">See all 9 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

